  <page id="2366">
    <name>Pro Tips: Making Math Matter</name>
    <intro></intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Pro%20Tip.png" alt="Hand with plant" width="140" height="136" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_middle"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use case studies in your instruction:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;To introduce or conclude an instructional topic, adults may&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;be engaged by a relevant situation&amp;nbsp;(case) because they can&amp;nbsp;then analyze that case to identify and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;practice applying potential&amp;nbsp;solutions (study).&amp;nbsp;We are using captioned video, along with access to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;a transcript, to support variability in all learners whatever their context. Because they are real-&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;life examples, case&amp;nbsp;studies that include multiple options for perception further&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;optimize&amp;nbsp;relevance, value, and authenticity in&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
                &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;learning.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/recruiting-interest/relevance-value-authenticity" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 7.2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use self-affirmation strategies to counterbalance stereotype threat:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Before learning about a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;new math concept, prompt students to reflect on their strengths, personal characteristics, skills,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;values, or roles they value and view as important. This kind of self-affirmation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;has been proven to reduce the anxiety caused by stereotype threats that can distract from&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;learning (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/recruiting-interest/threats-distractions" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 7.3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Model a growth mindset by saying “yes” to mathematical thinking:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Say “yes” to the act of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;thinking mathematically. That&amp;nbsp;doesn’t&amp;nbsp;mean saying a student is right when they provide an&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;answer that&amp;nbsp;does not&amp;nbsp;match up to accepted facts (2+2=4). It means showing respect for&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;students by inviting them to think through their assertions. This can create a safe space&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;where learners can explore creative&amp;nbsp;approaches to math without fear of being penalized for&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;any mistakes (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/recruiting-interest/threats-distractions" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 7.3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
                        &lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Use scaffolds to help learners reflect on their own math literacy:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Scaffolds are tools,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;structures, or strategies that we use to support learning while we build new skills.&amp;nbsp;A graphic&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;organizer is an example of a scaffold learners can use to support their working memory and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;executive functioning as they work to develop their problem-solving skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;in math (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Action &amp;amp; Expression&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression/executive-functions/information-resources/information-resources" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 6.3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Reframe your role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;With flipped learning, class time can be optimized to provide additional&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;opportunities for learners to apply what&amp;nbsp;they've&amp;nbsp;learned with support from not only you,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;but also their peers (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/effort-persistence/collaboration-community" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 8.3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;). &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
                    &lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;&lt;strong style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Make math relevant by using analogies:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Analogies help learners understand the structure of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;new information by relating it to what they already know. They can be motivating because&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;they increase the learner's belief that the new material is something they can master since it&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;feels like something&amp;nbsp;they have&amp;nbsp;already mastered (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/self-regulation/optimize-motivation" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 9.1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider%20wave.png" alt="Divider Wave" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
